  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You magically activate a wardstone, which lodges itself into position and weaves a spell over the area to block magical entry.</em></p><p><strong>Materials:</strong> You require a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.cB0Cwt5l7TefAUlC]{Wardstone} that weighs 10 lbs, typically valued at 500 gold. This spell doesn't consume the Wardstone, but the Wardstone cannot be used again until the spell ends.</p><p><strong>Ritual Casting Time</strong>: 1 Hour</p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>The Wardstone becomes immobile and emanates a magical field over an area. The area must fit inside a 1000 foot radius and not overlap with another Forbiddance effect.</p></li><li><p>Creatures can't teleport into the radius or enter the area through another plane. When you cast this spell, you designate a password or keyed item. A creature that speaks the password or carries the keyed item can bypass the Forbiddance spell.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Forbiddance can be ended by casting <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.piOfkIqVwkpV4Znb]{Break Enchantment}</em> on the wardstone. The caster can also end the spell by touching the Wardstone and saying a command word. Finally, the Wardstone can be destroyed with the <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.057CZWwhMSyXT0M3]{Disintegrate} </em>spell, which ends Forbiddance<em>.</em></p></li></ul>",
      "chat": "<p><strong>Materials:</strong> You require a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.cB0Cwt5l7TefAUlC]{Wardstone} that weighs 10 lbs, typically valued at 500 gold. This spell doesn't consume the Wardstone, but the Wardstone cannot be used again until the spell ends.</p><p><strong>Ritual Casting Time</strong>: 1 Hour</p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>The Wardstone becomes immobile and emanates a magical field over an area. The area must fit inside a 1000 foot radius and not overlap with another Forbiddance effect.</p></li><li><p>Creatures can't teleport into the radius or enter the area through another plane. When you cast this spell, you designate a password or keyed item. A creature that speaks the password or carries the keyed item can bypass the Forbiddance spell.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Forbiddance can be ended by casting <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.piOfkIqVwkpV4Znb]{Break Enchantment}</em> on the wardstone. The caster can also end the spell by touching the Wardstone and saying a command word. Finally, the Wardstone can be destroyed with the <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.057CZWwhMSyXT0M3]{Disintegrate} </em>spell, which ends Forbiddance<em>.</em></p></li></ul>"
